MSC21476 | Introduction to Dynamical SystemsThis Section Cancelled | https://enr-apps.as.cmu.edu/open/SOC/SOCServlet/courseDetails?COURSE=21476&SEMESTER=F15 | instructors:Kinderlehrer, David prereq:(21241 or 21242) and (21261) description:This course is an introduction to differentiable dynamical systems. The material includes basic properties of dynamical systems, including the existence and uniqueness theory, continuation, singular points, orbits, and their classification.  The Poincare'-Bendixson theorem and typical applications, like Lienard equations and Lotka-Volterra are also covered. An introduction to chaos as time permits.    3 hrs. lec.
MSC21484 | Graph Theory | https://enr-apps.as.cmu.edu/open/SOC/SOCServlet/courseDetails?COURSE=21484&SEMESTER=S16 | instructors:Pegden, Wesley prereq:(21228 or 15251) and (21241 or 21242) description:Graph theory uses basic concepts to approach a diversity of problems and nontrivial applications in operations research, computer science and other disciplines. It is one of the very few mathematical areas where one is always close to interesting unsolved problems. Topics include graphs and subgraphs, trees, connectivity, Euler tours and Hamilton cycles, matchings, graph colorings, planar graphs and Euler's Formula, directed graphs, network flows, counting arguments, and graph algorithms.  3 hrs. lec.
